President Trump and Prime Minister Johnson held a meeting and discussed various topics, including Brexit and trade. President Trump expressed his confidence in Johnson's ability to handle Brexit and praised him as the right man for the job. They also discussed the prospect of a trade deal between the US and the UK, with Trump stating that it would be bigger than any previous trade deal. They touched on the possibility of inviting Putin to the next G7 meeting and addressed the ongoing trade war with China. Trump defended the trade war, while Johnson expressed a desire for trade peace. They also confirmed that the NHS would be off the table in any trade talks between the US and the UK. Finally, they mentioned the progress on a trade deal with Japan, which they expect to announce soon.